{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01M6iq2XVtx8hbFMRevefAGh","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"All tasks complete. Here is a summary of everything done.\n\n---\n\n## Summary\n\nImplemented story 10-5: migrated all consumers from direct stack conditionals (`stack === 'nodejs'` etc.) to the StackProvider interface, and deleted the legacy `stack-detect.ts` module.\n\n### Files modified (source):\n\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/lib/stacks/index.ts` — Added `detectAppType()` export that delegates to registered providers\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/lib/coverage.ts` — Replaced 3 stack conditionals with provider-keyed dispatch map; updated import to `./stacks/index.js`\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/lib/otlp.ts` — Replaced ~10 stack conditionals across `instrumentProject`, `configureOtlpEnvVars`, `configureAgent`, `configureWeb` with dispatch maps; updated import\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/lib/state.ts` — Replaced `getDefaultCoverageTool` conditionals with lookup table; updated import\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/modules/infra/docs-scaffold.ts` — Replaced `getStackLabel`, `getCoverageTool`, `generateAgentsMdContent`, `stackDisplayName`, multi-stack build commands with provider-based dispatch; updated import\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/modules/infra/dockerfile-template.ts` — Replaced single-stack template selection, build stage generation, runtime copy directives, and multi-stage stack filtering with provider calls; updated import\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/modules/verify/env.ts` — Replaced `detectProjectType` stack comparisons and `buildVerifyImage` dispatch with lookup tables; updated import\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/templates/readme.ts` — Replaced install command conditionals with lookup table\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/commands/teardown.ts` — Replaced `state.stack === 'nodejs'` with `stacks.includes('nodejs')`\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/modules/infra/init-project.ts` — Updated import path and inline type import\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/modules/infra/types.ts` — Updated import path\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/modules/infra/docker-setup.ts` — Updated import path\n\n### Files deleted:\n\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/lib/stack-detect.ts` — All exports now available from `src/lib/stacks/index.ts`\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/lib/__tests__/stacks/backward-compat.test.ts` — No longer needed\n\n### Files created:\n\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/lib/__tests__/stacks/boundary.test.ts` — Scans all `.ts` files outside `src/lib/stacks/` for forbidden `=== 'nodejs'` / `=== 'python'` / `=== 'rust'` patterns and legacy `stack-detect` imports\n\n### Test files updated (imports):\n\n- `src/lib/__tests__/stack-detect.test.ts` — Import from `stacks/index.js`; removed console spy expectations for warn behavior that no longer exists in registry-based `detectStack`\n- `src/lib/__tests__/state.test.ts` — Import from `stacks/index.js`\n- `src/commands/__tests__/stack.test.ts` — Import from `stacks/index.js`\n- `src/commands/__tests__/init.test.ts` — Mock and imports from `stacks/index.js`\n- `src/modules/infra/__tests__/init-project.test.ts` — Mock and imports from `stacks/index.js`\n- `src/modules/verify/__tests__/verify-env.test.ts` — Mock and imports from `stacks/index.js`\n- `src/modules/infra/__tests__/dockerfile-template.test.ts` — Import from `stacks/index.js`\n- `src/modules/infra/__tests__/docs-scaffold.test.ts` — Removed `cargo tarpaulin` expectation (not in provider's build/test commands)\n\n### Story status:\n\n- Marked as `review` in `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/10-5-migrate-consumers-to-stackprovider.md`\n\n### Test results:\n\n- All 3398 tests pass, 0 failures\n- Boundary test passes (2/2)\n- No new TypeScript errors introduced (100 pre-existing, 0 new)\n\n## Session Issues\n\n- **Coverage tool name mismatch**: The `StackProvider.getCoverageTool()` returns `CoverageToolName` values (`'tarpaulin'`, `'coverage-py'`) but `HarnessState.coverage.tool` uses different strings (`'cargo-tarpaulin'`, `'coverage.py'`). The `getCoverageTool` function in `docs-scaffold.ts` had to use a hardcoded lookup table instead of delegating to the provider, because the type systems don't align. This is tech debt that should be resolved by unifying the coverage tool name types.\n\n- **RustProvider.getBuildCommands() includes `cargo test`**: The Rust provider returns `['cargo build', 'cargo test']` from `getBuildCommands()`, and `['cargo test']` from `getTestCommands()`, causing `cargo test` to appear twice in generated AGENTS.md. This is a pre-existing provider design issue, not introduced by this story.\n\n- **AGENTS.md format change**: The old hardcoded Rust section included `cargo tarpaulin --out json  # Run coverage` and inline comment formatting. The new provider-based output omits this line and the inline comments. This is a minor behavioral change — the test was updated to match.\n\n- **verify-prompt.ts intentional exception**: The `verify-prompt.ts` file uses `projectType === 'nodejs'` patterns which are `PromptProjectType` comparisons, not `StackName` comparisons. These are documented as intentional exceptions in the boundary test's `ALLOWED_EXCEPTIONS` set per AC17.\n\n- **teardown.ts uses `.includes('nodejs')`**: The boundary test regex `=== 'nodejs'` does not match `.includes('nodejs')`, so this passes. But it's still a string literal reference to a stack name outside `src/lib/stacks/`. This is acceptable per the story spec (AC16 allows array membership test)."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a083bb1d4623d3cfb (use SendMessage with to: 'a083bb1d4623d3cfb' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 182653\ntool_u