{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_014RzgPVnxXMxtBKGLV1ShDc","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_019A4HTgAxmdWjs5pNXjSaqP","name":"Edit","input":{"replace_all":false,"file_path":"/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/.session-issues.md","old_string":"- **Observation:** `otlp.ts` is heaviest migration target (~10 stack conditionals). `scanner.ts` had zero stack conditionals.","new_string":"- **Observation:** `otlp.ts` is heaviest migration target (~10 stack conditionals). `scanner.ts` had zero stack conditionals.\n\n### 10-5-migrate-consumers-to-stackprovider — dev-story (2026-03-24T09:55Z)\n\n- **Coverage tool name mismatch (tech debt):** `StackProvider.getCoverageTool()` returns `CoverageToolName` values (`'tarpaulin'`, `'coverage-py'`) but `HarnessState.coverage.tool` uses different strings (`'cargo-tarpaulin'`, `'coverage.py'`). Docs-scaffold had to use hardcoded lookup instead of provider delegation.\n- **RustProvider.getBuildCommands() duplication:** Returns `['cargo build', 'cargo test']` from `getBuildCommands()` and `['cargo test']` from `getTestCommands()`, causing `cargo test` to appear twice in generated AGENTS.md. Pre-existing provider design issue.\n- **AGENTS.md format change:** Old hardcoded Rust section had inline comments and `cargo tarpaulin` line. Provider-based output omits these. Minor behavioral change, test updated.\n- **verify-prompt.ts intentional exception:** Uses `projectType === 'nodejs'` (`PromptProjectType`, not `StackName`). Documented in boundary test's `ALLOWED_EXCEPTIONS` per AC17.\n- **teardown.ts uses `.includes('nodejs')`:** String literal reference to stack name outside `src/lib/stacks/`, but acceptable per AC16 (array membership test allowed)."},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1216,"cache_read_input_tokens":48747,"cache_crea