{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01NQFJhfdisZwxGgfMvJomZh","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Boundary test passes. Both assertions validated: zero stack string comparisons outside `src/lib/stacks/`, zero imports from `stack-detect.ts`.\n\n---\n\n**CODE REVIEW FINDINGS**\n\n**Story:** 10-5-migrate-consumers-to-stackprovider\n**Issues Found:** 0 High, 2 Medium (fixed), 3 Low (not fixed)\n\n**MEDIUM ISSUES (fixed):**\n\n1. **Unused import `_detectStack` in `src/lib/stacks/index.ts`** (line 27) — `detectStack as _detectStack` was imported but never referenced. Removed.\n\n2. **Stale comment in `src/lib/stacks/types.ts`** (line 4) — Referenced backward compat with `stack-detect.ts` which no longer exists after this story deleted it. Updated to reflect current state.\n\n**Review Outcome:** All HIGH and MEDIUM issues fixed. All ACs are implemented. All 3398 tests pass. Coverage at 96.98% (target 90%). All 129 files above 80% per-file floor. Boundary test confirms zero abstraction leaks. Story status updated to `verifying`.\n\n**Files modified during review:**\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/lib/stacks/index.ts` — removed unused import\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/lib/stacks/types.ts` — updated stale comment\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/10-5-migrate-consumers-to-stackprovider.md` — status changed to `verifying`\n\n## Session Issues\n\n**Bugs found and their severity:**\n- None (zero runtime bugs found)\n\n**Code quality issues found but NOT fixed (LOW priority items, tech debt):**\n- LOW: `coverage.ts` uses a local `coverageDetectors` dispatch map instead of delegating to `provider.detectCoverageConfig()` as suggested by AC1 wording. This is because the consumer's `CoverageToolInfo` type (with `runCommand`, `reportFormat`) differs from the provider's `CoverageToolInfo` type (with `configFile`). The dispatch map pattern is functionally correct and eliminates all `if (stack === ...)` conditionals. Resolving this would require extending the StackProvider interface or adding an adapter layer — a future refactoring opportunity.\n- LOW: `state.ts` `COVERAGE_TOOL_DEFAULTS`, `docs-scaffold.ts` `STATE_COVERAGE_TOOLS`, `readme.ts` `INSTALL_COMMANDS`, and `otlp.ts` dispatch maps all use stack name strings as object keys. These are structurally different from `=== 'nodejs'` conditional patterns (and pass the boundary test), but they create maintenance burden when adding new stacks. Each would need a new entry when a 4th stack is added.\n- LOW: `verify/env.ts` `STACK_TO_PROJECT_TYPE` map (line 70-74) maps stack names to ProjectType. This is redundant given that ProjectType and StackName share values, but serves as a controlled translation layer.\n\n**Coverage gaps:**\n- None. All 129 files above 80% per-file floor. Overall 96.98%.\n\n**Architecture concerns:**\n- The `CoverageToolInfo` type exists in two incompatible forms: `src/lib/coverage.ts` (consumer-facing, with `runCommand`/`reportFormat`) and `src/lib/stacks/types.ts` (provider-facing, with `configFile`). A unified type would enable true delegation per AC1's intent, but this is a pre-existing design decision, not introduced by this story.\n\n**Items sent back for re-development:**\n- None. All acceptance criteria are implemented and verified."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a78c38524a1df4229 (use SendMessage with to: 'a78c38524a1df4229' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 114264\ntool_uses: 75\nduration_ms: 486241</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"01d3be87-3cff-45e1-920c-7390a9e4093c","uuid":"4677d74a-2ec2-4162-97e5-a341341f45a6","timestamp":"2026-03-24T10:05:36.922Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Run /bmad-code-review for the story at _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/10-5-migrate-consumers-to-stackprovider.md — perform adversarial review, fix all HIGH and MEDIUM issues found. After fixi