{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01SZEKNqs3CsWnbLfzCoCVAD","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01A6jpe8AeUQo4tQVn2StFFY","name":"Edit","input":{"replace_all":false,"file_path":"/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/.session-issues.md","old_string":"- **teardown.ts uses `.includes('nodejs')`:** String literal reference to stack name outside `src/lib/stacks/`, but acceptable per AC16 (array membership test allowed).","new_string":"- **teardown.ts uses `.includes('nodejs')`:** String literal reference to stack name outside `src/lib/stacks/`, but acceptable per AC16 (array membership test allowed).\n\n### 10-5-migrate-consumers-to-stackprovider — code-review (2026-03-24T10:03Z)\n\n- **MEDIUM (fixed):** Unused import `_detectStack` in `src/lib/stacks/index.ts` — imported but never referenced.\n- **MEDIUM (fixed):** Stale comment in `src/lib/stacks/types.ts` — referenced deleted `stack-detect.ts`.\n- **LOW (not fixed):** `coverage.ts` uses local dispatch map instead of delegating to `provider.detectCoverageConfig()` — consumer `CoverageToolInfo` type differs from provider type. Future refactoring opportunity.\n- **LOW (not fixed):** Multiple files use stack name strings as object keys in dispatch maps. Maintenance burden when adding 4th stack.\n- **LOW (not fixed):** `verify/env.ts` `STACK_TO_PROJECT_TYPE` map is redundant given StackName/ProjectType value overlap.\n- **Architecture concern:** `CoverageToolInfo` exists in two incompatible forms (consumer vs provider). Pre-existing, not introduced by this story."},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1437,"cache_read_input_tokens":52200,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1437},"output_tokens":46,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"p