{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01BrRUEnEBGsEbRphC9kSCLS","type":"tool_result","content":"   100→- Look for keys starting with \"{{epic_number}}-\" (e.g., \"1-1-\", \"1-2-\", etc.)\n   101→- Exclude epic key itself (\"epic-{{epic_number}}\")\n   102→- Exclude retrospective key (\"epic-{{epic_number}}-retrospective\")\n   103→  </action>\n   104→\n   105→<action>Count total stories found for this epic</action>\n   106→<action>Count stories with status = \"done\"</action>\n   107→<action>Collect list of pending story keys (status != \"done\")</action>\n   108→<action>Determine if complete: true if all stories are done, false otherwise</action>\n   109→\n   110→<check if=\"epic is not complete\">\n   111→  <output>\n   112→Alice (Product Owner): \"Wait, Bob - I'm seeing that Epic {{epic_number}} isn't actually complete yet.\"\n   113→\n   114→Bob (Scrum Master): \"Let me check... you're right, Alice.\"\n   115→\n   116→**Epic Status:**\n   117→\n   118→- Total Stories: {{total_stories}}\n   119→- Completed (Done): {{done_stories}}\n   120→- Pending: {{pending_count}}\n   121→\n   122→**Pending Stories:**\n   123→{{pending_story_list}}\n   124→\n   125→Bob (Scrum Master): \"{user_name}, we typically run retrospectives after all stories are done. What would you like to do?\"\n   126→\n   127→**Options:**\n   128→\n   129→1. Complete remaining stories before running retrospective (recommended)\n   130→2. Continue with partial retrospective (not ideal, but possible)\n   131→3. Run sprint-planning to refresh story tracking\n   132→   </output>\n   133→\n   134→<ask if=\"{{non_interactive}} == false\">Continue with incomplete epic? (yes/no)</ask>\n   135→\n   136→  <check if=\"user says no\">\n   137→    <output>\n   138→Bob (Scrum Master): \"Smart call, {user_name}. Let's finish those stories first and then have a proper retrospective.\"\n   139→    </output>\n   140→    <action>HALT</action>\n   141→  </check>\n   142→\n   143→<action if=\"user says yes\">Set {{partial_retrospective}} = true</action>\n   144→<output>\n   145→Charlie (Senior Dev): \"Just so everyone knows, this partial retro might miss some important lessons from those pending stories.\"\n   146→\n   147→Bob (Scrum Master): \"Good point, Charlie. {user_name}, we'll document what we can now, but we may want to revisit after everything's done.\"\n   148→</output>\n   149→</check>\n   150→\n   151→<check if=\"epic is complete\">\n   152→  <output>\n   153→Alice (Product Owner): \"Excellent! All {{done_stories}} stories are marked done.\"\n   154→\n   155→Bob (Scrum Master): \"Perfect. Epic {{epic_number}} is complete and ready for retrospective, {user_name}.\"\n   156→</output>\n   157→</check>\n   158→\n   159→</step>\n   160→\n   161→<step n=\"0.5\" goal=\"Discover and load project documents\">\n   162→  <invoke-protocol name=\"discover_inputs\" />\n   163→  <note>After discovery, these content variables are available: {epics_content} (selective load for this epic), {architecture_content}, {prd_content}, {document_project_content}</note>\n   164→</step>\n   165→\n   166→<step n=\"2\" goal=\"Deep Story Analysis - Extract Lessons from Implementation\">\n   167→\n   168→<output>\n   169→Bob (Scrum Master): \"Before we start the team discussion, let me review all the story records to surface key themes. This'll help us have a richer conversation.\"\n   170→\n   171→Charlie (Senior Dev): \"Good idea - those dev notes always have gold in them.\"\n   172→</output>\n   173→\n   174→<action>For each story in epic {{epic_number}}, read the complete story file from {implementation_artifacts}/{{epic_number}}-{{story_num}}-*.md</action>\n   175→\n   176→<action>Extract and analyze from each story:</action>\n   177→\n   178→**Dev Notes and Struggles:**\n   179→\n   180→- Look for sections like \"## Dev Notes\", \"## Implementation Notes\", \"## Challenges\", \"## Development Log\"\n   181→- Identify where developers struggled or made mistakes\n   182→- Note unexpected complexity or gotchas discovered\n   183→- Record technical decisions that didn't work out as planned\n   184→- Track where estimates were way off (too high or too low)\n   185→\n   186→**Review Feedback Patterns:**\n   187→\n   188→- Look for \"## Review\", \"## Code Review\", \"## SM Review\", \"## Scrum Master Review\" sections\n   189→- Identify recurring feedback themes across stories\n   190→- Note which types of issues came up repeatedly\n   191→- Track quality concerns or architectural misalignments\n   192→- Document praise or exemplary work called out in reviews\n   193→\n   194→**Lessons Learned:**\n   195→\n   196→- Look for \"## Lessons Learned\", \"## Retrospective Notes\", \"## Takeaways\" sections within stories\n   197→- Extract explicit lessons documented during development\n   198→- Identify \"aha moments\" or breakthroughs\n   199→- Note what would be done differently"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01RgbEdgdZzBzTLJjLUk89Tw","session_id":"01d3be87-3cff-45e1-920c-7390a9e4093c","uuid":"71ab84f5-95b0-47e1-9cfb-71fdf63a58e1","timestamp":"2026-03-24T10:10:44.336Z"}
