{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_017U9y8p1JG18nW5giwRzoMa","type":"tool_result","content":"   200→- Track successful experiments or approaches\n   201→\n   202→**Technical Debt Incurred:**\n   203→\n   204→- Look for \"## Technical Debt\", \"## TODO\", \"## Known Issues\", \"## Future Work\" sections\n   205→- Document shortcuts taken and why\n   206→- Track debt items that affect next epic\n   207→- Note severity and priority of debt items\n   208→\n   209→**Testing and Quality Insights:**\n   210→\n   211→- Look for \"## Testing\", \"## QA Notes\", \"## Test Results\" sections\n   212→- Note testing challenges or surprises\n   213→- Track bug patterns or regression issues\n   214→- Document test coverage gaps\n   215→\n   216→<action>Synthesize patterns across all stories:</action>\n   217→\n   218→**Common Struggles:**\n   219→\n   220→- Identify issues that appeared in 2+ stories (e.g., \"3 out of 5 stories had API authentication issues\")\n   221→- Note areas where team consistently struggled\n   222→- Track where complexity was underestimated\n   223→\n   224→**Recurring Review Feedback:**\n   225→\n   226→- Identify feedback themes (e.g., \"Error handling was flagged in every review\")\n   227→- Note quality patterns (positive and negative)\n   228→- Track areas where team improved over the course of epic\n   229→\n   230→**Breakthrough Moments:**\n   231→\n   232→- Document key discoveries (e.g., \"Story 3 discovered the caching pattern we used for rest of epic\")\n   233→- Note when team velocity improved dramatically\n   234→- Track innovative solutions worth repeating\n   235→\n   236→**Velocity Patterns:**\n   237→\n   238→- Calculate average completion time per story\n   239→- Note velocity trends (e.g., \"First 2 stories took 3x longer than estimated\")\n   240→- Identify which types of stories went faster/slower\n   241→\n   242→**Team Collaboration Highlights:**\n   243→\n   244→- Note moments of excellent collaboration mentioned in stories\n   245→- Track where pair programming or mob programming was effective\n   246→- Document effective problem-solving sessions\n   247→\n   248→<action>Store this synthesis - these patterns will drive the retrospective discussion</action>\n   249→\n   250→<output>\n   251→Bob (Scrum Master): \"Okay, I've reviewed all {{total_stories}} story records. I found some really interesting patterns we should discuss.\"\n   252→\n   253→Dana (QA Engineer): \"I'm curious what you found, Bob. I noticed some things in my testing too.\"\n   254→\n   255→Bob (Scrum Master): \"We'll get to all of it. But first, let me load the previous epic's retro to see if we learned from last time.\"\n   256→</output>\n   257→\n   258→</step>\n   259→\n   260→<step n=\"3\" goal=\"Load and Integrate Previous Epic Retrospective\">\n   261→\n   262→<action>Calculate previous epic number: {{prev_epic_num}} = {{epic_number}} - 1</action>\n   263→\n   264→<check if=\"{{prev_epic_num}} >= 1\">\n   265→  <action>Search for previous retrospectives using pattern: {implementation_artifacts}/epic-{{prev_epic_num}}-retro-*.md</action>\n   266→\n   267→  <check if=\"previous retrospectives found\">\n   268→    <output>\n   269→Bob (Scrum Master): \"I found our retrospectives from Epic {{prev_epic_num}}. Let me see what we committed to back then...\"\n   270→    </output>\n   271→\n   272→    <action>Read the previous retrospectives</action>\n   273→\n   274→    <action>Extract key elements:</action>\n   275→    - **Action items committed**: What did the team agree to improve?\n   276→    - **Lessons learned**: What insights were captured?\n   277→    - **Process improvements**: What changes were agreed upon?\n   278→    - **Technical debt flagged**: What debt was documented?\n   279→    - **Team agreements**: What commitments were made?\n   280→    - **Preparation tasks**: What was needed for this epic?\n   281→\n   282→    <action>Cross-reference with current epic execution:</action>\n   283→\n   284→    **Action Item Follow-Through:**\n   285→    - For each action item from Epic {{prev_epic_num}} retro, check if it was completed\n   286→    - Look for evidence in current epic's story records\n   287→    - Mark each action item: ✅ Completed, ⏳ In Progress, ❌ Not Addressed\n   288→\n   289→    **Lessons Applied:**\n   290→    - For each lesson from Epic {{prev_epic_num}}, check if team applied it in Epic {{epic_number}}\n   291→    - Look for evidence in dev notes, review feedback, or outcomes\n   292→    - Document successes and missed opportunities\n   293→\n   294→    **Process Improvements Effectiveness:**\n   295→    - For each process change agreed to in Epic {{prev_epic_num}}, assess if it helped\n   296→    - Did the change improve velocity, quality, or team satisfaction?\n   297→    - Should we keep, modify, or abandon the change?\n   298→\n   299→    **Technical Debt Status:**"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01RgbEdgdZzBzTLJjLUk89Tw","session_id":"01d3be87-3cff-45e1-920c-7390a9e4093c","uuid":"a7ae194b-78b7-4cdd-ba92-715ca3be3d0b","timestamp":"2026-03-24T10:10:48.154Z"}
