{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01SWSKurYAvTT4tv5RRaW1Ec","type":"tool_result","content":"   300→    - For each debt item from Epic {{prev_epic_num}}, check if it was addressed\n   301→    - Did unaddressed debt cause problems in Epic {{epic_number}}?\n   302→    - Did the debt grow or shrink?\n   303→\n   304→    <action>Prepare \"continuity insights\" for the retrospective discussion</action>\n   305→\n   306→    <action>Identify wins where previous lessons were applied successfully:</action>\n   307→    - Document specific examples of applied learnings\n   308→    - Note positive impact on Epic {{epic_number}} outcomes\n   309→    - Celebrate team growth and improvement\n   310→\n   311→    <action>Identify missed opportunities where previous lessons were ignored:</action>\n   312→    - Document where team repeated previous mistakes\n   313→    - Note impact of not applying lessons (without blame)\n   314→    - Explore barriers that prevented application\n   315→\n   316→    <output>\n   317→\n   318→Bob (Scrum Master): \"Interesting... in Epic {{prev_epic_num}}'s retro, we committed to {{action_count}} action items.\"\n   319→\n   320→Alice (Product Owner): \"How'd we do on those, Bob?\"\n   321→\n   322→Bob (Scrum Master): \"We completed {{completed_count}}, made progress on {{in_progress_count}}, but didn't address {{not_addressed_count}}.\"\n   323→\n   324→Charlie (Senior Dev): _looking concerned_ \"Which ones didn't we address?\"\n   325→\n   326→Bob (Scrum Master): \"We'll discuss that in the retro. Some of them might explain challenges we had this epic.\"\n   327→\n   328→Elena (Junior Dev): \"That's... actually pretty insightful.\"\n   329→\n   330→Bob (Scrum Master): \"That's why we track this stuff. Pattern recognition helps us improve.\"\n   331→</output>\n   332→\n   333→  </check>\n   334→\n   335→  <check if=\"no previous retro found\">\n   336→    <output>\n   337→Bob (Scrum Master): \"I don't see a retrospective for Epic {{prev_epic_num}}. Either we skipped it, or this is your first retro.\"\n   338→\n   339→Alice (Product Owner): \"Probably our first one. Good time to start the habit!\"\n   340→</output>\n   341→<action>Set {{first_retrospective}} = true</action>\n   342→</check>\n   343→</check>\n   344→\n   345→<check if=\"{{prev_epic_num}} < 1\">\n   346→  <output>\n   347→Bob (Scrum Master): \"This is Epic 1, so naturally there's no previous retro to reference. We're starting fresh!\"\n   348→\n   349→Charlie (Senior Dev): \"First epic, first retro. Let's make it count.\"\n   350→</output>\n   351→<action>Set {{first_retrospective}} = true</action>\n   352→</check>\n   353→\n   354→</step>\n   355→\n   356→<step n=\"4\" goal=\"Preview Next Epic with Change Detection\">\n   357→\n   358→<action>Calculate next epic number: {{next_epic_num}} = {{epic_number}} + 1</action>\n   359→\n   360→<output>\n   361→Bob (Scrum Master): \"Before we dive into the discussion, let me take a quick look at Epic {{next_epic_num}} to understand what's coming.\"\n   362→\n   363→Alice (Product Owner): \"Good thinking - helps us connect what we learned to what we're about to do.\"\n   364→</output>\n   365→\n   366→<action>Attempt to load next epic using selective loading strategy:</action>\n   367→\n   368→**Try sharded first (more specific):**\n   369→<action>Check if file exists: {planning_artifacts}/epic*/epic-{{next_epic_num}}.md</action>\n   370→\n   371→<check if=\"sharded epic file found\">\n   372→  <action>Load {planning_artifacts}/*epic*/epic-{{next_epic_num}}.md</action>\n   373→  <action>Set {{next_epic_source}} = \"sharded\"</action>\n   374→</check>\n   375→\n   376→**Fallback to whole document:**\n   377→<check if=\"sharded epic not found\">\n   378→<action>Check if file exists: {planning_artifacts}/epic*.md</action>\n   379→\n   380→  <check if=\"whole epic file found\">\n   381→    <action>Load entire epics document</action>\n   382→    <action>Extract Epic {{next_epic_num}} section</action>\n   383→    <action>Set {{next_epic_source}} = \"whole\"</action>\n   384→  </check>\n   385→</check>\n   386→\n   387→<check if=\"next epic found\">\n   388→  <action>Analyze next epic for:</action>\n   389→  - Epic title and objectives\n   390→  - Planned stories and complexity estimates\n   391→  - Dependencies on Epic {{epic_number}} work\n   392→  - New technical requirements or capabilities needed\n   393→  - Potential risks or unknowns\n   394→  - Business goals and success criteria\n   395→\n   396→<action>Identify dependencies on completed work:</action>\n   397→\n   398→- What components from Epic {{epic_number}} does Epic {{next_epic_num}} rely on?\n   399→- Are all prerequisites complete and stable?"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01RgbEdgdZzBzTLJjLUk89Tw","session_id":"01d3be87-3cff-45e1-920c-7390a9e4093c","uuid":"5c26a1e4-b440-42a9-95a7-e0c2abe530b8","timestamp":"2026-03-24T10:10:52.012Z"}
