{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01H5cpaeHw5GK5odfgi7dhSi","type":"tool_result","content":"   500→{{list_technical_prereqs}}\n   501→\n   502→Bob (Scrum Master): \"And here's what's coming next. Epic {{next_epic_num}} builds on what we just finished.\"\n   503→\n   504→Elena (Junior Dev): \"Wow, that's a lot of dependencies on our work.\"\n   505→\n   506→Charlie (Senior Dev): \"Which means we better make sure Epic {{epic_number}} is actually solid before moving on.\"\n   507→{{/if}}\n   508→\n   509→═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n   510→\n   511→Bob (Scrum Master): \"Team assembled for this retrospective:\"\n   512→\n   513→{{list_participating_agents}}\n   514→\n   515→Bob (Scrum Master): \"{user_name}, you're joining us as Project Lead. Your perspective is crucial here.\"\n   516→\n   517→{user_name} (Project Lead): [Participating in the retrospective]\n   518→\n   519→Bob (Scrum Master): \"Our focus today:\"\n   520→\n   521→1. Learning from Epic {{epic_number}} execution\n   522→   {{#if next_epic_exists}}2. Preparing for Epic {{next_epic_num}} success{{/if}}\n   523→\n   524→Bob (Scrum Master): \"Ground rules: psychological safety first. No blame, no judgment. We focus on systems and processes, not individuals. Everyone's voice matters. Specific examples are better than generalizations.\"\n   525→\n   526→Alice (Product Owner): \"And everything shared here stays in this room - unless we decide together to escalate something.\"\n   527→\n   528→Bob (Scrum Master): \"Exactly. {user_name}, any questions before we dive in?\"\n   529→</output>\n   530→\n   531→<action>WAIT for {user_name} to respond or indicate readiness</action>\n   532→\n   533→</step>\n   534→\n   535→<step n=\"6\" goal=\"Epic Review Discussion - What Went Well, What Didn't\">\n   536→\n   537→<output>\n   538→Bob (Scrum Master): \"Let's start with the good stuff. What went well in Epic {{epic_number}}?\"\n   539→\n   540→Bob (Scrum Master): _pauses, creating space_\n   541→\n   542→Alice (Product Owner): \"I'll start. The user authentication flow we delivered exceeded my expectations. The UX is smooth, and early user feedback has been really positive.\"\n   543→\n   544→Charlie (Senior Dev): \"I'll add to that - the caching strategy we implemented in Story {{breakthrough_story_num}} was a game-changer. We cut API calls by 60% and it set the pattern for the rest of the epic.\"\n   545→\n   546→Dana (QA Engineer): \"From my side, testing went smoother than usual. The dev team's documentation was way better this epic - actually usable test plans!\"\n   547→\n   548→Elena (Junior Dev): _smiling_ \"That's because Charlie made me document everything after Story 1's code review!\"\n   549→\n   550→Charlie (Senior Dev): _laughing_ \"Tough love pays off.\"\n   551→</output>\n   552→\n   553→<action>Bob (Scrum Master) naturally turns to {user_name} to engage them in the discussion</action>\n   554→\n   555→<output>\n   556→Bob (Scrum Master): \"{user_name}, what stood out to you as going well in this epic?\"\n   557→</output>\n   558→\n   559→<action>WAIT for {user_name} to respond - this is a KEY USER INTERACTION moment</action>\n   560→\n   561→<action>After {user_name} responds, have 1-2 team members react to or build on what {user_name} shared</action>\n   562→\n   563→<output>\n   564→Alice (Product Owner): [Responds naturally to what {user_name} said, either agreeing, adding context, or offering a different perspective]\n   565→\n   566→Charlie (Senior Dev): [Builds on the discussion, perhaps adding technical details or connecting to specific stories]\n   567→</output>\n   568→\n   569→<action>Continue facilitating natural dialogue, periodically bringing {user_name} back into the conversation</action>\n   570→\n   571→<action>After covering successes, guide the transition to challenges with care</action>\n   572→\n   573→<output>\n   574→Bob (Scrum Master): \"Okay, we've celebrated some real wins. Now let's talk about challenges - where did we struggle? What slowed us down?\"\n   575→\n   576→Bob (Scrum Master): _creates safe space with tone and pacing_\n   577→\n   578→Elena (Junior Dev): _hesitates_ \"Well... I really struggled with the database migrations in Story {{difficult_story_num}}. The documentation wasn't clear, and I had to redo it three times. Lost almost a full sprint on that story alone.\"\n   579→\n   580→Charlie (Senior Dev): _defensive_ \"Hold on - I wrote those migration docs, and they were perfectly clear. The issue was that the requirements kept changing mid-story!\"\n   581→\n   582→Alice (Product Owner): _frustrated_ \"That's not fair, Charlie. We only clarified requirements once, and that was because the technical team didn't ask the right questions during planning!\"\n   583→\n   584→Charlie (Senior Dev): _heat rising_ \"We asked plenty of questions! You said the schema was finalized, then two days into development you wanted to add three new fields!\"\n   585→\n   586→Bob (Scrum Master): _intervening calmly_ \"Let's take a breath here. This is exactly the kind of thing we need to unpack.\"\n   587→\n   588→Bob (Scrum Master): \"Elena, you spent almost a full sprint on Story {{difficult_story_num}}. Charlie, you're saying requirements changed. Alice, you feel the right questions weren't asked up front.\"\n   589→\n   590→Bob (Scrum Master): \"{user_name}, you have visibility across the whole project. What's your take on this situation?\"\n   591→</output>\n   592→\n   593→<action>WAIT for {user_name} to respond and help facilitate the conflict resolution</action>\n   594→\n   595→<action>Use {user_name}'s response to guide the discussion toward systemic understanding rather than blame</action>\n   596→\n   597→<output>\n   598→Bob (Scrum Master): [Synthesizes {user_name}'s input with what the team shared] \"So it sounds like the core issue was {{root_cause_based_on_discussion}}, not any individual person's fault.\"\n   599→\n   600→Elena (Junior Dev): \"That makes sense. If we'd had {{preventive_measure}}, I probably could have avoided those redos.\"\n   601→\n   602→Charlie (Senior Dev): _softening_ \"Yeah, and I could have been clearer about assumptions in the docs. Sorry for getting defensive, Alice.\"\n   603→\n   604→Alice (Product Owner): \"I appreciate that. I could've been more proactive about flagging the schema additions earlier, too.\"\n   605→\n   606→Bob (Scrum Master): \"This is good. We're identifying systemic improvements, not assigning blame.\"\n   607→</output>\n   608→\n   609→<action>Continue the discussion, weaving in patterns discovered from the deep story analysis (Step 2)</action>\n   610→\n   611→<output>\n   612→Bob (Scrum Master): \"Speaking of patterns, I noticed something when reviewing all the story records...\"\n   613→\n   614→Bob (Scrum Master): \"{{pattern_1_description}} - this showed up in {{pattern_1_count}} out of {{total_stories}} stories.\"\n   615→\n   616→Dana (QA Engineer): \"Oh wow, I didn't realize it was that widespread.\"\n   617→\n   618→Bob (Scrum Master): \"Yeah. And there's more - {{pattern_2_description}} came up in almost every code review.\"\n   619→\n   620→Charlie (Senior Dev): \"That's... actually embarrassing. We should've caught that pattern earlier.\"\n   621→\n   622→Bob (Scrum Master): \"No shame, Charlie. Now we know, and we can improve. {user_name}, did you notice these patterns during the epic?\"\n   623→</output>\n   624→\n   625→<action>WAIT for {user_name} to share their observations</action>\n   626→\n   627→<action>Continue the retrospective discussion, creating moments where:</action>\n   628→\n   629→- Team members ask {user_name} questions directly\n   630→- {user_name}'s input shifts the discussion direction\n   631→- Disagreements arise naturally and get resolved\n   632→- Quieter team members are invited to contribute\n   633→- Specific stories are referenced with real examples\n   634→- Emotions are authentic (frustration, pride, concern, hope)\n   635→\n   636→<check if=\"previous retrospective exists\">\n   637→  <output>\n   638→Bob (Scrum Master): \"Before we move on, I want to circle back to Epic {{prev_epic_num}}'s retrospective.\"\n   639→\n   640→Bob (Scrum Master): \"We made some commitments in that retro. Let's see how we did.\"\n   641→\n   642→Bob (Scrum Master): \"Action item 1: {{prev_action_1}}. Status: {{prev_action_1_status}}\"\n   643→\n   644→Alice (Product Owner): {{#if prev_action_1_status == \"completed\"}}\"We nailed that one!\"{{else}}\"We... didn't do that one.\"{{/if}}\n   645→\n   646→Charlie (Senior Dev): {{#if prev_action_1_status == \"completed\"}}\"And it helped! I noticed {{evidence_of_impact}}\"{{else}}\"Yeah, and I think that's why we had {{consequence_of_not_doing_it}} this epic.\"{{/if}}\n   647→\n   648→Bob (Scrum Master): \"Action item 2: {{prev_action_2}}. Status: {{prev_action_2_status}}\"\n   649→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01RgbEdgdZzBzTLJjLUk89Tw","session_id":"01d3be87-3cff-45e1-920c-7390a9e4093c","uuid":"a50989a6-96d1-4d34-8232-9daf158bff47","timestamp":"2026-03-24T10:11:06.687Z"}
